{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "22", "m": "03", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "14", "M": "17", "S": "40"}}, "news": [{"title": "NCLT allows withdrawal of insolvency proceedings against ATS Knightsbridge", "para": "NCLT has permitted the withdrawal of insolvency proceedings against Noida's ATS Knightsbridge residential project after a settlement with lenders. The Corporate Insolvency Resolution Process, initiated in 2023, was formally closed on March 13, 2026. The project is nearing completion, with a tentative handover expected in 18-24 months.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/nclt-approves-withdrawal-of-insolvency-for-ats-knightsbridge-project/129733914?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-69340/129733914.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Vedanta moves NCLAT, challenges NCLT nod to Adani's bid for acquiring Jaiprakash Associates", "para": "Vedanta Group has appealed to the NCLAT against the NCLT's decision. The NCLT had approved Adani Group's bid to acquire Jaiprakash Associates Ltd. Vedanta was also in the race to acquire the company. The Committee of Creditors had previously approved Adani's plan. Jaiprakash Associates has significant assets across real estate, cement, and hospitality.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/vedanta-moves-nclat-challenges-nclt-nod-to-adanis-bid-for-acquiring-jaiprakash-associates/129732622?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-21524/129732622.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}, {"title": "Chandigarh housing board to hike restoration charges for resumed properties", "para": "Chandigarh Housing Board is set to significantly hike restoration charges for properties resumed due to dues or violations, potentially by \u20b91 lakh to \u20b93 lakh. This move aims to curb unauthorized construction and encourage timely payments. Meanwhile, the administration seeks approval to regularize GPA property transfers, expecting to recover substantial lost revenue from stamp duty.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/chandigarh-housing-board-announces-up-to-7-hike-in-restoration-charges-for-resumed-properties/129733375?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-28968/129733375.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}